<h1 id="node-jquery">node-jQuery</h1>

<p>A stupid-simple wrapper over jQuery for  Node.JS (server). Currently 1.7.2.</p>

<h2 id="node-js">Node.JS</h2>

<p>npm install jQuery</p>

<p>var $ = require(&lsquo;jQuery&rsquo;);</p>

<h2 id="examples">Examples</h2>

<p>$(&ldquo;<h1>test passes</h1>&rdquo;).appendTo(&ldquo;body&rdquo;);
    console.log($(&ldquo;body&rdquo;).html());</p>

<p>In Node.JS you may also create separate window instances</p>

<p>var jsdom = require(&#39;jsdom&rsquo;).jsdom
      , myWindow = jsdom().createWindow()
      , $ = require(&#39;jQuery&rsquo;)
      , jq = require(&#39;jQuery&rsquo;).create()
      , jQuery = require(&#39;jQuery&rsquo;).create(myWindow)
      ;</p>

<p>$(&ldquo;<h1>test passes</h1>&rdquo;).appendTo(&ldquo;body&rdquo;);
    console.log($(&ldquo;body&rdquo;).html());</p>

<p>jq(&ldquo;<h2>other test passes</h2>&rdquo;).appendTo(&ldquo;body&rdquo;);
    console.log(jq(&ldquo;body&rdquo;).html());</p>

<p>jQuery(&ldquo;<h3>third test passes</h3>&rdquo;).appendTo(&ldquo;body&rdquo;);
    console.log(jQuery(&ldquo;body&rdquo;).html());</p>

<p>Output:</p>

<p><h1>test passes</h1>
    <h2>other test passes</h2>
    <h3>third test passes</h3></p>

<h2 id="jsonp-example">JSONP Example</h2>

<p>var $ = require(&#39;jQuery&rsquo;);</p>

<p>$.getJSON(&#39;http://twitter.com/status/user_timeline/treason.json?count=10&amp;callback=?&rsquo;,function(data) {
      console.log(data);
    });</p>
